            "title": "Japan's Budget Will Consider Fiscal Sustainability, Fin Min Katayama Says",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Megumi Fujikawa </p><br/><p>\n  TOKYO--Japan's Finance Minister Satsuki Katayama said the government will carefully consider fiscal discipline as worries over the nation's debt conditions have driven a sharp increase in government bond yields. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  \"We are, of course, giving due consideration to fiscal sustainability in the budget drafting\" for the next fiscal year, Katayama said at a news conference on Friday. </p><p>\n\n  JGB yields have hit multiyear highs across the curve in recent days, reflecting fiscal concerns and expectations for a December rate hike by the Bank of Japan. </p><p>\n\n  The benchmark 10-year JGB yield hit 1.940%, the highest level since July 2007, on Friday morning. </p><p>\n\n  While JGB yields are determined in the market based on various factors, the government will pay careful attention to market movements, Katayama said. </p><p>\n\n  Katayama, however, refrained from talking directly about monetary policy, reiterating that specific measures are up to the BOJ to decide. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Megumi Fujikawa at megumi.fujikawa@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  12-04-25 2028ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/japan-s-budget-will-consider-fiscal-sustainability-fin-min-katayama-says-ce7d51dcd98df32d",
            "pub_date": "2025-12-05 09:30:53",
